{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, Shan et al.",
    "found that this approach outperformed the DDSP additive model in terms of reconstruction error when using 20 wavetables, and performed almost equivalently with only 10 wavetables.",
    "Further, this method provided a roughly 12× improvement in inference speed, although as the authors note this is likely to be related to the 10-fold decrease in the number of parameter sequences that require interpolation.",
    "The implementations discussed thus far are all, in a sense, constrained additive models.",
    "This is because a harmonic relationship between sinusoidal component frequencies is enforced."
  ]
}